review_blob: Bottle in Salzburg. A refreshing summer beer. Definitely makes up for its price but not the best beer for sure. Lacks a strong aroma, a clear golden look, minimal head. A sweet refreshing taste. A light body and thin texture with soft carbonation and an easy ending. An enjoyable beer in hot summer days, not the best quality though.

Bready aroma, quite hoppy and bitter. Doesnt go down easily. A clear golden color. Hard to describe the taste, sugary (includes sugar, yes) but still bitter. Bad palate, definitely leaves a bad taste in mouth. I dont suggest this beer for sure.
